{"pagelen": 100, "values": [{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/hoffmanlab/segway/issues/47/comments/21650175.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/hoffmanlab/segway/issues/47#comment-21650175"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/hoffmanlab/segway/issues/47.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 47, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/hoffmanlab/segway.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/hoffmanlab/segway"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{68bf38bf-f0c1-4c9c-909e-0ee4b2c26257}ts=python"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "segway", "full_name": "hoffmanlab/segway", "uuid": "{68bf38bf-f0c1-4c9c-909e-0ee4b2c26257}"}, "title": "Better handling when --ruler is set and no segment table is specified"}, "content": {"raw": "This would be good. The reason this is specified in the seg table is I wanted to preserve the ability to maybe have a different ruler for different segment labels. We haven't needed that so far. This might be a backward- and forward-compatible solution:\n\n* if there is no step specified in a seg table, just use what's specified by `--ruler`\n* remove the step from the default seg table", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>This would be good. The reason this is specified in the seg table is I wanted to preserve the ability to maybe have a different ruler for different segment labels. We haven't needed that so far. This might be a backward- and forward-compatible solution:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>if there is no step specified in a seg table, just use what's specified by <code>--ruler</code></li>\n<li>remove the step from the default seg table</li>\n</ul>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2015-09-09T16:19:56.528322+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Michael Hoffman", "uuid": "{ffa8e039-5d4d-4f69-a4ba-ac25cbaf700b}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bffa8e039-5d4d-4f69-a4ba-ac25cbaf700b%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bffa8e039-5d4d-4f69-a4ba-ac25cbaf700b%7D/"}, "ava